Nyara, no disrespect meant. No condescending attitude meant either. A guild is an organization of people that devote their time to eachother, and together accomplish the more difficult things in EQ. And if you are implying the guild which I am a member of is not responsible to its members and to the server, you are wrong.<br>
 I have backed up the calendar numerous times. Deris and I (and others) have been at eachothers throats a number of times, BECAUSE he felt the calendar would just be abused and missused. I see that happening with open raids. There will always be an influx of planes capable people and guilds, no matter which server we play on, and those 10 or so guilds that can do a raid self sufficiently will grow to 11, then 12, then 13 etc. What I am saying is; those who wish to obtain items from one of the planes/uber mobs, should either be able to do it all in-guild, or be able to ask assistance/join another guild for a raid or two. Open raids are crowding an already crowded calendar. It is not doing justice to the organization the calendar provides. <br>
<br>
