</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucalidornrealmweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calidorn Realmweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/01 6:31:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Open raids...</span><hr size=1> I've been on a few open raids and the word &quot;open&quot; was misused.  If an epic item was dropped it was already designated to a person.  If a person needed only one item to complete their planar gear then they got the item.<br>
<br>
It would be polite to say that you can have the epic item since you are close or that you can have the piece of armor since it is the last one you need...<br>
BUT that is not an open raid!<br>
<br>
An open raid should be just that, open to all who wish to attend.  None of the &quot;open raid for all except Calidorn or anyone else.  (hehe and no I have never been told that just an example)<br>
<br>
If an item drops then all who need it should random.  It should not be given out by the person hosting the raid as it has with some &quot;open raids&quot; because that is biased.  If someone attends then they should have the opportunity to roll for it if they need it.  Whether it be equipment or item for an epic quest.  They need epic items as much as the person who only has two items left to complete.<br>
<br>
If 1/4th of the people on the raid are of the same guild as the person who sponsored it I would have to say it would be an outcry of abuse.  Not that they do not have the right as anyone else to go on open raids but it is pretty much a sign that the open raid was designated as a way for that guild to have a greater chance of obtaining planar items.<br>
<br>
I've had friends leave open raids because the person who sponsored it set up groups and needless to say one group was the guild of the person who set it up... and was also the KS group.  The leader of the group would loot and at times would call out loot and other times another person from that group would loot after the leader did, saying that there was an item on the corpse and the leader had all slots full.  Odd that the people that looted corpses were of the class that could use the equipment if it dropped.<br>
<br>
Are open raids abused?  Yes they are.<br>
<br>
Does anyone actually do real &quot;open raids&quot;?  Yes they do<br>
<br>
The problem I see is that most people are either saying there is a problem and they need to stop it or that it is fine and leave it alone.  It's not a white/black issue but it is grey at the current moment.  Luclin has already unleashed the hordes of 50+ people.  Hell many people have two characters of plane level now.  Heck some with two level 60's.  *hug papazol*  (Any man who can remove his visible armor and solo the entrance of Sebilis to the bridge deserves respect!)<br>
<br>
What I also see is a new generation of people who are planes ready yet are planes inexperienced.  For them, open raids are the only way that they will be able to get plane equipment.  They might not have the guild, the friends, the connections to go any other way.  Perhaps when they asked to join your guild they were turned down because they were level 50 with an oracle robe and staff of writhing.<br>
<br>
What I would like to see is a list of guilds that would be willing to take people, that are not of their guild, to planes and other raids.  I am going to post a note on general and if your guild does do this please post saying so.  Just thought it would be nice to actually have a list of some sort showing which guilds will do this.  I know it might cause some tells and maybe some rudeness of people if you do not need those classes or if they want you to stop the raid so they can come join late.  The reason why I ask this is that people who are not in big guilds or are unguilded may have a chance to experience a well planned and balanced raid.<br>
<br>
I'll quit rambling for now just thought I'd add some.<br>
<br>
Calidorn Realmweaver the 56 Insidiousless and guildless enchanter<br>
